description: Andrew doesn’t always make the best choices (see Season 6). And now Buffy finds herself and the very course of her life profoundly affected by one of Andrew’s over-the-top, idiotic . . .hair-brained . . . schemes. Together with Andrew and Spike, the worried Slayer will have to confront herself and her comrades, as well as a long-standing annoyance, the number-one Buffy hater of all Buffy haters: Simone, the gun-toting Slayer.
name: Apart (of Me), Part Two

description:
The Red Hulk is here, and the Hood is back! A new adventure begins as the Illuminati are reformed, and the menace of the Infinity Gems returns! Steve Rogers confronts Iron Man as the truth is finally exposed!

Includes material reprinted from Avengers #7-9.

The story of one man's desire to clear his good name. The reclusive Dr. Doug is named as the source for the mysterious Plaque epidemic, which has infected the Earth in mostrous proportions. Enlisting the aid of five teenagers to battle the plaque, Dr. Doug shrinks the newly formed Plaque Patrol, and injects them into his own body, after infecting himself with the deviant strain of Plaque X.

The borders between the Earthly and Spirit worlds are cracked - and the fault lies right beneath Shinjuku! The town is crawling with demons, and one of them has placed a deadly curse on the President of Earth's ruling federation. Doom is on the horizon! Fortunately, Kyoya Izayoi is no ordinary high school kid - he's heir to the rare martial art Nenpo, and he wields the mystical sword Ashura! Together with Sayaka Rama, the brave and resourceful daughter of Earth's President, he's taking on Levi Rah, master of the demons and maker of the deadly curse!
name: Volume 1

description: A terrifying trip into Demon City! High-school martial arts expert Kyoya Izayoi is struggling to save the President of Earth from an evil curse placed by the sorcerer Levy Rah. Kyoya, the President's lovely daughter Sayaka and Kyoya's friend Sam are headed into the heart of Demon City to battle Rah and his demon bodyguards. It's not going to be easy - even before they get there, they encounter a battle, and Sayaka has an eye-opening strategy for ending the fight!
name: Volume 2

description: The Hwan-Woong dynasty is in turmoil. General Hae-Mo-Soo has taken control of most of the land. Prince Chi-Woo, ruler of the Hwan-Woong dynasty, is so severely depressed by the hardships he's suffered during the Revolution that he has become almost non-functional. It's in this state that the prince is discovered by Gat, a peasant and close friend of the Prince. Gat rescues Chi-Woo from General Hae-Mo-Soo's men, but the danger is not over yet. Though Hae-Mo-Soo and Chi-Woo both lay claim to power, there can be only one ruler of the land. Gat and Chi-Woo begin their journey together, enduring heartache and hardship as they seek to reclaim the Prince's rightful place on the throne.
name: Volume 1

description: Will the Jew-Shin Empire crumble right before its heir's eyes? General Hae-Mo-Soo's stranglehold on the Hwan-Woong Dynasty appears secure, while traumatic delusions leave Prince Chi-Woo helpless. Gat's still standing, sword drawn and ready to take Duke Geh-Ru down - but will he be able to thwart the malevolent sorcery impeding his designs? Blood will flow as valor seeks to prevail against the enemies of the withering State!
name: Volume 2

description:
An otherworldly invasion beset the Earth at the close of the Pacific War in 1945. Droves of Phantom Beasts waged a bitter struggle against the already war-weary inhabitants of Earth. This uncommon insurgency forced humanity to unite and defend a world already in the throes of turmoil. The death toll decimated military forces leaving Japan with no choice but to enlist the help of its teenage population. Atsushi Hayami is amongst the ranks of those who, rather than lead a normal high school life, takes up arms to ensure the survival of mankind.

Episode #1-8.
name: Volume 1

description:
Full Phantom Force! Fifty years since the invasion, the Phantom Beasts continue their devastating onslaught, indiscriminately seeking to decimate the human race into extinction. With the military's body-count rising, Japan was forced to enlist teenagers into battle. Mai Shibamura and Atsushi Hayami, two young soldiers of Unit 5121, have finally seen some action and are ready to take on even more Phantom Beasts. While trying to secure food supplies, they notice that the alien invaders are attacking cats, which fuels Shibamura's anger. Later, in the Arakawa war zone, orders and inexperience lead to tragedy and humiliation for Unit 5121, and both Hayami and Shibamura feel the sting of loss. This setback weakens the platoon...but not for long! The existence of the human race is at stake, and these kids were drafted to save it!

Episode #9-16.
name: Volume 2

description:
The war against the Phantom Beasts rages on, and absolute victory for Army Unit 5121 seems impossible. Hayami's latest preoccupation with heroism won't stop the enemy from easing its way through the gun smoke, and these extraterrestrial invaders don't play by the rules of war! With enough bone-splitting mecha under their belts to flatten the teenage troops, the Phantom Beasts will stop at nothing to annihilate the soldiers of Earth! Packed with enough mecha action to top Mobile Suit Gundam: Seed and Megazone!

Episode #17-26 (Final Episode).
name: Volume 3
Maid in the Morgue
Anubis Lord of Death

description:
As co-creator of Judge Dredd, Carlos Ezquerra is responsible for the future lawman’s iconic design, bringing a European sensibility to Britain’s most famous comic character. Now you can witness the power of the master at work in this collection of modern Dredd stories. From the aftermath of Judgement Day in ‘The Taking of Sector House 123’ to the tough justice of Cursed Earth Koburn this Graphic Novel contains the very best work of a true original.

With stories by John Wagner (A History of Violence), Garth Ennis (Preacher) and Gordon Rennie (Caballistics Inc.).

This volume includes:

  • THE TAKING OF SECTOR 123 (Judge Dredd Megazine 2.10-2.11)
  • HELTER SKELTER (2000AD progs 1250-1261)
  • THE GIRLFRIEND (Judge Dredd Megazine 4.15)
  • PHARTZ (Judge Dredd Megazine 201)
  • STURM UND DANG (Judge Dredd Megazine 211-212)
  • KUSS HARD (Judge Dredd Megazine 221-223)
  • BURIAL PARTY (Judge Dredd Megazine 228)
  • THE ASSIZES (Judge Dredd Megazine 239)
  • MALACHI (Judge Dredd Megazine 241-244)

Plus:

  • Creator Bios
  • Gallery
name: The Carlos Ezquerra Collection

Most American presidents are given, at most, a period of eight years in which to protect a single country. But unknown to the public at large, one rough-riding president took it upon himself to protect the whole known universe for the entire expanse of time. What do a man who was formerly president and an inventor who was formerly alive get up to when they obtain a stolen time machine? Science, that's what. THIS ISSUE: Teddy Roosevelt and the ghost of Thomas Edison travel to the far-flung future on a wager, only to discover the terrible secret of space! It's a rough and tumble tale of science with both fists as our two heroes race through time to liberate the Red Planet from its foreign invaders.
Tattoo arrives in New Orleans and assists a gang of humans called Blues before continuing her quest for the "Gatekeeper".

Channeling his inner Indiana Jones, TV's original caped crusader faces his biggest challenge yet in ancient Egypt. Like sands through the hourglass has never rung truer. And we're talking a pretty big hourglass.

High Priestess of the Snake People (7 pages) - In the Swiss Alps, a young American stumbles across a cult of snake-worshipers. He is bewitched by the beautiful snake queen Gilda. An old villager comes to his help and blows the whole bunch to kingdom come with a pack of dynamite.

True Tales of the Supernatural #1 (1 page) - "Among a certain noble family of Scotland, there was a legend..." If a family member hears the beating of drums, another member is stricken by tragic death. It so happens.

The Ghost in the Portrait (7 pages) - A young couple free the ghost of an evil ancestor. He takes revenge on the bones of the people who sentenced him to death. Then he commands the man to murder his wife, as he did with his wife. The woman manages to destroy the evil spirit in the last moment. The couple lives happily ever after.

True Tales of the Supernatural #2 (1 page) - "There is a legend about a ghost-infested cell in a jail in New Orleans..." The inhabitants of this cell become suicidal because of the ghost of an old woman who hanged herself in it.

Villa of the Vampire (7 pages) - A vampire haunts an Italian villa. The inhabitants are decimated. With the help of a doctor and a blood transfusion, the husband can save his wife and kill the creature of darkness.

Text Story: Unburied Dead (2 pages) - Man hypnotizes wife, but summons demon in the process. They fight over possession of the woman's body. Her body explodes. Man is arrested and sentenced to death.

No Grave to Hold Him (7 pages) - To live on after his demise, the brain of a dying professor is planted into the body of an executed criminal. His gangster pals kidnap him to find the hidden money from their last robbery. Dramatic showdown on an airfield landing strip. The bad guys are killed, the professor's assistant regains control over the Frankenstein-like creature. Hidden from the public, it lives on scribbling formulas.
name: Villa of the Vampire

description: The ghosts of a remote past are roaming among the masks of Lucerne’s Carnival: a beautiful witch and the “tempestarius”, a storm-maker who went to the stake for her love... Between imaginary storms and wrenched hearts, panic is spreading. To save a friend in danger, Harlan and Tesla will have to face the Evil incarnate of a gathering of witches, who serve their worst enemy...
name: Carnevale di spettri

description: In Belgrade, the psychiatrist of young Danica thinks the vampires are a fantasy of her subconscious, a projection of the girl’s guilt. But Danica is a normal girl, with nothing to blame herself for. Where do the nightmares and the sense of panic, that now seize her even when she’s awake, come from? Who is the obsessed and guilty alter ego that lives in those hallucinating and dark dreams, as if it was a second life beyond a looking-glass? Her therapists has no doubts about it: in a few session of regressive hypnosis they’ll get to the source of the problem and her disorders will end. Or else... it will be the beginning of something far more horrible... The only therapy for it? The intervention of a vampire-hunters team!
name: La donna nello specchio

description: Between the old warehouses on the River Thames, the Gothic palace of Lord Marsden is hidden to anyone who can’t see through illusions. When a self-proclaimed vampirologist from London, Jack Tarrant, finds the mansion while investigating about South Seas Company’s property, Harlan Draka decides to pay a courtesy call to his arch-nemesis. Their appointment is to be postponed to another time and place, in a past resurfaced through the encounter between Bram Stoker, the writer of “Dracula”, and the legendary traveller, Arminius Vambèry. A past that will lead Harlan from the steppes of the “Lord of Death”, Erlik Khan, to the wolf-infested woods of Transylvania...
name: I vampiri di Londra

description: Drummond School, in Dorset, is an institution with a noble and ancient tradition. When some of its young students are ensnarled by a trap set by the Master of the Night, Lord Marsden, strange and unherad of events take place. Only an alliance between Dampyr and co. and some of the most brilliant minds in London can save the kids: a bunch of brave people will have to cross the borders of time and space...
name: La notte dei pipistrelli

description: Gaslights, carriages, sailing ships moored on the Thames’ docks, and the sinister underworld of Whitechapel... Who’s the blood-thirsty killer that’s menacing London? According to Bram Stoker and professor Vambéry, it’s the Master of the Night, Draka. And according to Harlan? While looking for the disappeared kids, Dampyr begins to have doubts about the true identity of his enemy. Those who stay in a parallel world for a long time, are at risk of losing memory of what things were like... Having severed his psychic contacts with his friends in our world, Harlan increasingly sees all his certainties and memories vanish, except maybe for the name of his greatest enemy...
name: Città di ombre

description: Scattered in a parallel world that resembles the 1890s London, Harlan and his friends erased all their memories of who they are and where they come from. But they still are sure of one thing: they know they’re vampire hunters, there to eliminate a dangerous Master of the Night. Along with their new friends, Bram Stoker and Arminius Vambéry, Harlan and Tesla (under their new identities of Van Helsing and Mina Harker) enter the fortified palace of Carfax to kill the vampire, Draka! He’s not Harlan’s father, but an identical alter ego. But Lord Marsden knows that if Harlan will kill this “twin”, the Draka of our world would be severely weakened... If the Dampyr, the true one, would die, Marsden’s triumph would be even more absolute... Meanwhile, Kurjak, Hulagu and Murphy are caught by Marsden himself and his cruel godson Morningstar...
name: Harlan contro Draka
